[Student "W"]
{[showcards S:C2]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \SJ, the \SK is played from dummy and holds the trick. Next come dummy's \HK, then another trump to North's \HA.

At trick 4 North plays the \C2 from his hand and you must decide what to play.

Play the \C3 (smoothly).

North has 2 small \Cs and faces a choice of dummy plays in the suit. He must decide whether to play you for the \CA or the \CQ. If you play your \CA you make the decision very easy for him.

When you correctly play your small \C life becomes harder for North. Sometimes he will guess correctly and play dummy's \CK, but other times he will play dummy's \CJ, hoping you have the \CQ.}
[Play "W"]SJ

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:KQJ.AK73.QT94.73 T8762.T54.K6.J96 54.J62.J852.AKQ2 A93.Q98.A73.T854"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "c74de5374d34b2d6883dce3d1cfa1684000d60d28cdd619662964f2b7c7bb478"]
[Category "Defense"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "defense/second_hand_play"]
[Student "E"]
{[showcards N:D2]

You are North. The bidding has been as shown.

Partner led the \S6. You won the \SA and returned the \S9, won by East's \SQ.

East next played to dummy's \CA and led the \D2. What do you play?

Play the \DA.

Count the points. East's 15-17 plus West's 11 plus your 10 comes to 36-38. So South has room for an Ace or a King, but no more.

South's second \S play was the 2, so it looks like he started with 5 \Ss. And the fall of East's \Ss looks like he may have 1 \S left, very likely the \SK.

All this means that you should take your \DA now and return your last \S to establish South's suit. Now South's \DK will be an entry to the \Ss

If you play low, South will have to take the \DK now, and although he can play a \S to establish the suit, he will not have an entry to be able to cash them.}
[Play "W"]S6

